reviewText: It's not HD, but it's very informative and provides a lot of information about Cocos Island. Worth watching.

I've watched this twice and Cocos Island is on my bucket list. Want to do a Live Aboard! (National Geographic also has a very good detail of this area, describes how it has been protected from fishermen and the thriving underwater life!)
I didn't want to see the boat interior, divers and where they ate and rested and then there was the diving equipment. Just show us the underwater marine life.

I've been lucky enough to dive Cocos Island twice. (2007 - 2009) The main attraction there is big fish and especially schooling Hammerheads. If you buy a DVD about Cocos, that's what you want to see. Unfortunately the DVD has to little good big fish action.
